    public abstract class AbstractRDKitCalculatorNodeModel
extends AbstractRDKitNodeModel
    This class adds functionality common to a Calculator node. This is a node that adds normally additionally columns to an input table calculating their values based on input columns.
    Author:
    Manuel Schwarze

        protected AbstractRDKitCalculatorNodeModel(int nrInDataPorts,
                                           int nrOutDataPorts)
        Creates a new node model with the specified number of input and output ports. Enables distribution and streaming by default for nodes, that have exactly one input port and one output port and have no pre-processing and post-processing implemented. If distribution and streaming shall be handled differently a node implementation should call the other constructor and specify input and output port roles specifically.
        Parameters:
        nrInDataPorts - Number of input ports. Must be 0 .. n.
        nrOutDataPorts - Number of output ports. Must be 0 .. m.

    • Method Detail

      • autoEnableDistributionAndStreaming

        protected boolean autoEnableDistributionAndStreaming()
        Checks preconditions for distribution and streaming, and if they are fulfilled, enables these capabilities for this node. The preconditions are: Node overwrites method #createStreamableOperator(PartitionInfo, PortObjectSpec[]). Node has one input port. Node has one output port. Node does not do any preprocessing (method AbstractRDKitNodeModel.getPreProcessingPercentage() returns 0.0d). Node does not do any postprocessing (method AbstractRDKitNodeModel.getPostProcessingPercentage() returns 0.0d).. If node would support distribution and streaming, this method will call AbstractRDKitNodeModel.setPortRoles(InputPortRole[], OutputPortRole[]) with appropriate roles, otherwise it would call this method with null values, which would lead to the KNIME default behavior (no streaming, no distribution). Derived classes which want to change the default behavior can override this method.
        Returns:
        True, if distribution and streaming has been enabled. False otherwise.

      • enableDistributionAndStreaming

        protected void enableDistributionAndStreaming()
        Enables programmatically distribution and streaming for all ports. Should be called by nodes, which do not fulfil the conditions for auto-enabling of distribution and streaming, but still provide that capability.

      • createStreamableOperatorForCalculator

        protected StreamableOperator createStreamableOperatorForCalculator(PartitionInfo partitionInfo,
                                                                   PortObjectSpec[] inSpecs)
                                                            throws InvalidSettingsException
        The default implementation for providing distribution and streaming capabilities for an RDKit Calculator node. This should be called from the #createStreamableOperator(PartitionInfo, PortObjectSpec[]) method, which must be overwritten by every node model that supports streaming. This implementation checks if the node has been enabled for distribution and streaming and returns the appropriate StreamableOperator.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException

        protected DataTableSpec getOutputTableSpec(int outPort,
                                           DataTableSpec[] inSpecs)
                                    throws InvalidSettingsException
        Returns the output table specification of the specified out port. This implementation works based on a ColumnRearranger and delivers only a specification for out port 0, based on an input table on in port 0. Override this method if other behavior is needed.

        inSpecs - All input table specifications.

        Throws:

      • createOutputFactories

        protected abstract AbstractRDKitCellFactory[] createOutputFactories(int outPort,
                                                                    DataTableSpec inSpec)
                                                             throws InvalidSettingsException
        This method needs to be implemented by a concrete node to generate cell factories for all output tables. As there can be more than one factory specified to generate cells for a table, it returns for one output port an array of factories. However, usually only one element will be contained in this array.
        Parameters:
        outPort - The port number of the output table to create factories for.
        inSpec - Specification of the table to be merged with new columns that will be generated by the factories. Can be null.
        Returns:
        An array of factory objects. Should not return null. If no factories are used, it should return an empty array.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - Thrown, if creation of output factories fails.

      • getContextStatistics

        Returns:
        Context statistics. Can be null.

      • createColumnRearranger

        protected ColumnRearranger createColumnRearranger(int outPort,
                                                  DataTableSpec inSpec)
                                           throws InvalidSettingsException
        Creates a column rearranger based on all cell factories that are delivered by a call to #createOutputFactories(int)). These factories (usually there is just one) implement the logic to calculate new cells based on the input defined by the input data info objects delivered by a call to AbstractRDKitNodeModel.createInputDataInfos(DataTableSpec[]).
        Parameters:
        outPort - The output port of the node the column rearranger shall be created for. This value is used to create the output factories - a call is made to #createOutputFactories(int) with this outPort id.
        inSpec - The specification of the table the result column rearranger shall be based on. Must not be null.
        contextStatistics - When a column arranger gets created for streaming a context statistics object can be handed over here to be used in the first cell factory to count processed rows. Can be null.
        Returns:
        Column Rearranger for the specified input table.
        Throws:
        InvalidSettingsException - Thrown, if invalid settings are encountered while creating and gathering all necessary information in order to create the column rearranger object.

      • processing

        protected BufferedDataTable[] processing(BufferedDataTable[] inData,
                                         InputDataInfo[][] arrInputDataInfo,
                                         ExecutionContext exec)
                                  throws java.lang.Exception
        This method gets called from the method AbstractRDKitNodeModel.execute(BufferedDataTable[], ExecutionContext) to perform the main work of the node. It is equivalent to the original KNIME execute method. However, in this implementation the execute method acts more like a director to coordinate pre-, core and post-processing and to cleanup RDKit objects at the end. Hence, it should not be overridden. Instead a developer would override this method.
        Specified by:
        processing in class AbstractRDKitNodeModel
        Parameters:
        inData - The input tables of the node.
        arrInputDataInfo - Information about all columns of the input tables.
        exec - The execution context, which was derived as sub-execution context. Track the progress from 0..1.
        Returns:
        The result tables to be passed to the method AbstractRDKitNodeModel.postProcessing(BufferedDataTable[], InputDataInfo[][], BufferedDataTable[], ExecutionContext). If this method is not overridden these are the same tables that will be returned by the method AbstractRDKitNodeModel.execute(BufferedDataTable[], ExecutionContext) as the final result tables.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Thrown, if post-processing fails.
